252
00:17:10,945 --> 00:17:13,423
Four A and B. I'll take your coats.

253
00:17:14,815 --> 00:17:17,076
- Fasten your seat belts.
- Champagne, please.

254
00:17:17,251 --> 00:17:19,425
- It's free, isn't it?
- Oh, yes.

255
00:17:20,425 --> 00:17:21,382
We made it.

256
00:17:21,600 --> 00:17:22,948
Do you believe it?

257
00:17:23,948 --> 00:17:25,382
Hope we didn't forget anything.

258
00:18:46,319 --> 00:18:47,405
Mom?

259
00:18:55,016 --> 00:18:58,321
- That's real. It's real crystal.
- Yeah, so?

260
00:18:58,582 --> 00:19:01,408
- Put them in your purse.
- Frank, I can't do that.

261
00:19:01,627 --> 00:19:04,366
Just... Put them in your purse!

262
00:19:04,758 --> 00:19:07,149
Yeah. Fill it up.
Fill it up.

263
00:19:07,367 --> 00:19:08,672
Fill it up, please.

264
00:19:09,803 --> 00:19:10,802
Thank you.

265
00:19:11,021 --> 00:19:14,456
Don't you feel like a heel, flying
first class with the kids in coach?

266
00:19:14,631 --> 00:19:16,109
No. The kids are fine.

267
00:19:16,283 --> 00:19:20,588
The only time I ever flew as a kid was
in the station wagon, not to France.

268
00:19:20,893 --> 00:19:23,676
We had to go to Aunt Laura
and Uncle Arthur's.

269
00:19:24,329 --> 00:19:27,198
Kids are okay. They're having
the time of their lives.

270
00:19:28,242 --> 00:19:29,851
Hello?

271
00:19:31,417 --> 00:19:32,721
Mom?

272
00:19:35,157 --> 00:19:36,591
Dad?

273
00:19:45,465 --> 00:19:47,378
Where are you guys?

274
00:19:48,291 --> 00:19:49,683
Buzz?

275
00:20:02,860 --> 00:20:04,121
Megan?

276
00:20:04,557 --> 00:20:05,949
Hello?

277
00:20:08,862 --> 00:20:10,166
Rod?

278
00:20:10,341 --> 00:20:11,775
Uncle Frank?

279
00:20:11,993 --> 00:20:14,515
Uncle Frank, is this a joke?

280
00:20:16,168 --> 00:20:19,385
Megan? Linnie?

281
00:20:21,692 --> 00:20:23,735
Is this a joke?

282
00:20:47,351 --> 00:20:49,264
It's only my imagination.

283
00:20:49,482 --> 00:20:51,351
Only my imagination.

284
00:21:08,705 --> 00:21:11,922
The cars are still here.
They didn't go to the airport!

285
00:21:29,884 --> 00:21:33,319
I made my family disappear.

286
00:21:34,711 --> 00:21:36,625
<i>You're completely helpless.</i>

287
00:21:36,798 --> 00:21:37,799
<i>You know, Kevin...</i>

288
00:21:37,972 --> 00:21:41,625
<i>... you're what the French call
les incompetents.</i>

289
00:21:41,887 --> 00:21:44,801
<i>Kevin, I'm going to feed you
to my tarantula.</i>

290
00:21:44,975 --> 00:21:47,888
<i>Kevin, you are such a disease.</i>

291
00:21:48,063 --> 00:21:53,021
<i>There are 15 people, and you're
the only one who has to make trouble.</i>

292
00:21:53,282 --> 00:21:56,760
<i>Look what you did, you little jerk!</i>

293
00:22:00,370 --> 00:22:03,936
I made my family disappear.

294
00:22:18,027 --> 00:22:19,723
I'm free!

295
00:22:31,857 --> 00:22:32,988
Wow!

296
00:22:40,033 --> 00:22:43,077
No clothes on anybody.
Sickening!

297
00:22:44,252 --> 00:22:46,165
Cool! Firecrackers!

298
00:22:46,339 --> 00:22:47,861
I'll save these for later.

299
00:22:48,296 --> 00:22:51,036
Buzz, I'm going through
all your private stuff.

300
00:22:51,167 --> 00:22:53,819
You better come out and pound me!

301
00:22:57,820 --> 00:23:00,820
Buzz, your girlfriend! Woof!

302
00:23:49,791 --> 00:23:51,181
<i>Who is it?</i>

303
00:23:54,749 --> 00:23:56,227
<i>It's me. Snakes.</i>

304
00:23:56,401 --> 00:23:57,705
<i>I got the stuff.</i>

305
00:23:57,924 --> 00:24:00,750
<i>Leave it on the doorstep
and get the hell out of here.</i>

306
00:24:00,968 --> 00:24:04,185
<i>All right, Johnny,
but what about my money?</i>

307
00:24:04,360 --> 00:24:05,359
<i>What money?</i>

308
00:24:05,578 --> 00:24:07,795
<i>A.C. Said you had some dough for me.</i>

309
00:24:08,013 --> 00:24:10,927
<i>Is that a fact?
How much do I owe you?</i>

310
00:24:11,144 --> 00:24:13,058
<i>A.C. Said ten percent.</i>

311
00:24:14,233 --> 00:24:16,624
<i>Too bad A.C. Ain't in charge no more.</i>

312
00:24:17,450 --> 00:24:19,841
Guys, I'm eating junk
and watching rubbish!

313
00:24:20,017 --> 00:24:22,408
You better come out and stop me!

314
00:24:22,843 --> 00:24:24,886
<i>He'll call you when he gets out.</i>

315
00:24:27,888 --> 00:24:30,063
<i>I'll tell you what I'm gonna
give you.</i>

316
00:24:31,759 --> 00:24:33,976
<i>I'm gonna give you to
the count of ten...</i>

317
00:24:34,716 --> 00:24:37,021
<i>... to get your ugly, yellow...</i>

318
00:24:37,238 --> 00:24:39,413
<i>... no-good keister off my property...</i>

319
00:24:39,630 --> 00:24:41,587
<i>... before I pump your guts
full of lead.</i>

320
00:24:41,805 --> 00:24:43,239
<i>All right, I'm sorry.</i>

321
00:24:43,632 --> 00:24:44,457
<i>I'm going.</i>

322
00:24:44,676 --> 00:24:46,980
<i>One, two... ten.</i>

323
00:25:02,332 --> 00:25:04,637
<i>Keep the change,
you filthy animal.</i>

324
00:25:06,463 --> 00:25:07,680
Mom!

325
00:25:19,032 --> 00:25:20,424
What's the matter?

326
00:25:21,859 --> 00:25:22,990
Honey?

327
00:25:24,339 --> 00:25:26,861
I have a terrible feeling.

328
00:25:27,034 --> 00:25:27,947
About what?

329
00:25:29,470 --> 00:25:31,122
That we didn't do something.

330
00:25:32,080 --> 00:25:34,558
You feel that way because
we left in a hurry.

331
00:25:34,776 --> 00:25:36,471
We took care of everything.

332
00:25:36,732 --> 00:25:37,993
Did I turn off the coffee?

333
00:25:38,385 --> 00:25:39,559
No.

334
00:25:39,951 --> 00:25:40,864
I did.

335
00:25:41,081 --> 00:25:42,559
Did you lock up?

336
00:25:43,952 --> 00:25:45,082
Yeah.

337
00:25:46,474 --> 00:25:47,822
Did you close the garage?

338
00:25:49,824 --> 00:25:50,954
That's it.

339
00:25:51,172 --> 00:25:53,520
I forgot to close the garage.
That's it.

340
00:25:59,348 --> 00:26:01,131
No, that's not it.

341
00:26:03,174 --> 00:26:05,000
What else could we be forgetting?

342
00:26:08,916 --> 00:26:09,872
Kevin!

343
00:26:53,535 --> 00:26:56,753
The captain's doing all he can.
Your phones are out of order.

344
00:26:56,971 --> 00:26:59,493
We'll call when we land.
I'm sure it's okay.

345
00:27:01,234 --> 00:27:03,233
Horrible. Horrible.

346
00:27:03,712 --> 00:27:04,973
Just horrible.

347
00:27:05,409 --> 00:27:07,931
How could we do this?
We forgot him.

348
00:27:08,148 --> 00:27:10,583
We didn't forget him,
we just miscounted.

349
00:27:11,497 --> 00:27:13,975
What kind of mother am I?

350
00:27:14,194 --> 00:27:17,760
If it makes you feel any better,
I forgot my reading glasses.

351
00:27:22,370 --> 00:27:25,240
<i>Five families gone
on one block alone.</i>

352
00:27:25,457 --> 00:27:28,371
<i>They all told me from their
own mouths.</i>

353
00:27:28,588 --> 00:27:30,110
<i>It's almost too easy.</i>

354
00:27:30,676 --> 00:27:31,763
Check it out:

355
00:27:32,024 --> 00:27:34,068
All the houses with nobody home...

356
00:27:34,199 --> 00:27:37,069
...have automatic timers
on their lights.

357
00:27:37,461 --> 00:27:40,678
But I got it all figured out.
Watch this.

358
00:27:41,940 --> 00:27:46,898
Number 664 will be going on
right about...

359
00:27:48,289 --> 00:27:49,463
...now.

360
00:27:50,507 --> 00:27:52,464
Wait, wait, wait.

361
00:27:53,508 --> 00:27:56,552
Number 682...

362
00:27:57,379 --> 00:27:59,858
...right now.

363
00:28:02,207 --> 00:28:03,337
Wait a minute.

364
00:28:03,599 --> 00:28:06,382
681...

365
00:28:06,860 --> 00:28:07,729
...now.

366
00:28:10,208 --> 00:28:13,774
And that's the one, Marvin.
That's the silver tuna.

367
00:28:14,209 --> 00:28:15,426
It's very G.

368
00:28:16,036 --> 00:28:18,515
Very G, huh? It's loaded.

369
00:28:18,733 --> 00:28:20,994
It's got lots of top-flight goods.

370
00:28:21,168 --> 00:28:24,516
- Stereos, VCRs...
- Toys?

371
00:28:24,778 --> 00:28:27,300
Probably looking at some
very fine jewelry.

372
00:28:27,735 --> 00:28:29,169
Possible cash horde.

373
00:28:29,823 --> 00:28:32,389
Odd marketable securities.

374
00:28:32,954 --> 00:28:35,302
Who knows? It's a gem.

375
00:28:36,128 --> 00:28:38,085
Grab your crowbar.

376
00:28:39,043 --> 00:28:40,739
Crowbars up.

377
00:28:43,131 --> 00:28:47,522
<i>You're a rotter,
Mr. Grinch</i>

378
00:28:47,914 --> 00:28:51,611
<i>You're the king
Of sinful sots</i>

379
00:28:52,133 --> 00:28:54,308
<i>Your heart's a dead tomato</i>

380
00:28:54,525 --> 00:28:59,048
<i>Blotched with moldy purple spots,
Mr. Grinch</i>

381
00:29:40,059 --> 00:29:41,058
Which way?

382
00:29:41,712 --> 00:29:44,060
We'll go around back,
down the basement.

383
00:30:04,935 --> 00:30:07,718
- You said they were gone.
- They were gonna leave today.

384
00:30:07,936 --> 00:30:09,544
Let's get out of here.

385
00:30:46,033 --> 00:30:48,338
We have to use the phone, please.

386
00:30:49,164 --> 00:30:51,904
It's an emergency.
We really have to make a call.

387
00:30:52,078 --> 00:30:54,600
Please! Our brother's home alone.

388
00:30:55,210 --> 00:30:57,079
Give us the phone!

389
00:30:57,427 --> 00:30:58,601
I'm sorry. Thank you.

390
00:30:58,862 --> 00:31:01,471
I'm calling the police.
Book us a flight home.

391
00:31:01,689 --> 00:31:04,603
Get change out of here.
Call everybody you know.

392
00:31:04,778 --> 00:31:08,909
Here's my address book. You and Frank
call everyone on our street.

393
00:31:09,083 --> 00:31:10,952
Maybe somebody can help us.

394
00:31:11,127 --> 00:31:14,518
Hello? Hello?
Oh, she'll have to call you back.

395
00:31:20,955 --> 00:31:22,259
This is ridiculous.

396
00:31:22,434 --> 00:31:24,783
Only a wimp would be
hiding under a bed.

397
00:31:25,000 --> 00:31:28,958
And I can't be a wimp.
I'm the man of the house.

398
00:31:36,307 --> 00:31:39,656
Hey, I'm not afraid anymore!

399
00:31:40,656 --> 00:31:44,265
I said, I'm not afraid anymore!

400
00:31:44,745 --> 00:31:48,615
Do you hear me?
I'm not afraid anymore.

401
00:32:19,275 --> 00:32:20,492
Village police department.

402
00:32:20,754 --> 00:32:24,146
I'm calling from Paris.
I have a son who's home alone.

403
00:32:24,364 --> 00:32:29,322
<i>I'd like somebody to go there. Tell
him that we're coming home to get him.</i>

404
00:32:29,496 --> 00:32:33,062
Okay, let me connect you
with Family Crisis Intervention.

405
00:32:33,279 --> 00:32:34,714
Hold on.

406
00:32:36,628 --> 00:32:40,019
Larry, can you pick up?
There's some hyper lady on hold.

407
00:32:40,238 --> 00:32:42,672
- What line, Rose?
- Two.

408
00:32:43,326 --> 00:32:45,717
Family Crisis Intervention,
Sergeant Balzac.

409
00:32:45,892 --> 00:32:48,805
I'm calling from Paris.
I have a son who's home alone.

410
00:32:49,023 --> 00:32:53,719
Has the child been involved in
violence with a drunk family member?

411
00:32:53,937 --> 00:32:54,893
No!

412
00:32:55,198 --> 00:32:57,764
Has he been involved
in a household accident?

413
00:32:57,938 --> 00:33:00,069
I don't know. I hope not.

414
00:33:01,418 --> 00:33:05,505
Has the child ingested any poison
or is an object lodged in his throat?

415
00:33:05,723 --> 00:33:09,201
No, he's home alone! I'd like
somebody to go over to the house...

416
00:33:09,420 --> 00:33:11,116
...and see if he's all right.

417
00:33:12,246 --> 00:33:15,855
You want us to go to your house,
just to check on him.

418
00:33:16,073 --> 00:33:17,247
Yes!

419
00:33:18,030 --> 00:33:19,378
Let me connect you to the police.

420
00:33:19,596 --> 00:33:21,030
They just transferred me.

421
00:33:21,249 --> 00:33:22,205
- Rose!
- Yeah.

422
00:33:22,379 --> 00:33:23,422
- Hyper.
- Hang on.

423
00:33:23,597 --> 00:33:27,206
- Hold on, please.
- No, please don't hang up. Please!

424
00:33:27,989 --> 00:33:29,337
Any luck?

425
00:33:31,078 --> 00:33:33,730
- I couldn't get anybody.
- Leslie?

426
00:33:33,947 --> 00:33:36,208
Nothing but a bunch
of answering machines.

427
00:33:38,427 --> 00:33:41,385
Somebody pick up. Pick up!

428
00:33:41,602 --> 00:33:43,602
Oh, hi, ma'am. It's you again.

429
00:33:43,777 --> 00:33:47,734
Look, I'm calling from Paris.
I have a son who's home alone, and l...

430
00:33:47,908 --> 00:33:51,648
We'll send a policeman over
to your house to check on your son.

431
00:34:22,004 --> 00:34:24,613
There's nobody home.
The house looks secure.

432
00:34:24,788 --> 00:34:26,875
Tell them to count their kids again.

433
00:34:28,050 --> 00:34:30,528
You can't bump somebody or ask or...?

434
00:34:30,658 --> 00:34:32,571
There's no way I can do that.

435
00:34:32,702 --> 00:34:34,877
Isn't there a way
if you ask somebody?

436
00:34:35,094 --> 00:34:36,529
If you said it's an emergency...

437
00:34:36,747 --> 00:34:38,139
I cannot ask them.

438
00:34:38,357 --> 00:34:40,531
She's sending a policeman
over to the house.

439
00:34:40,749 --> 00:34:43,618
Well, that's a relief.
Everything here is booked.

440
00:34:43,836 --> 00:34:44,923
Nothing to Chicago?

441
00:34:45,185 --> 00:34:48,359
There's nothing to Chicago,
New York, Nashville.

442
00:34:49,794 --> 00:34:52,881
- What about a private plane?
- Sorry. We don't do that.

443
00:34:53,056 --> 00:34:56,013
The only thing is a booking
for us on Friday morning.

444
00:34:56,187 --> 00:34:58,709
Friday morn... That's two days away.

445
00:34:58,928 --> 00:35:00,884
The kids are exhausted and so are you.

446
00:35:01,102 --> 00:35:03,015
There's nothing we can do here.

447
00:35:03,233 --> 00:35:07,842
I say we go over to Rob's, and that
way we can call the police again.

448
00:35:08,060 --> 00:35:11,321
I'm not leaving here unless
it's on an airplane.

449
00:35:11,495 --> 00:35:13,539
Madame, we are doing
everything we can.

450
00:35:13,757 --> 00:35:17,757
If you want to stay at the airport,
maybe we can get you on standby.

451
00:35:18,020 --> 00:35:20,933
It is a possibility
that a seat will open up.

452
00:35:21,628 --> 00:35:24,542
- Is that okay?
- Yes. I'll wait.

453
00:35:31,066 --> 00:35:32,458
I'll miss you, honey.

454
00:35:36,459 --> 00:35:38,155
Don't you get lost.

455
00:35:39,807 --> 00:35:40,894
Goodbye.

456
00:35:56,812 --> 00:36:00,030
I took a shower, washing every
body part with actual soap.

457
00:36:00,247 --> 00:36:01,987
Including all my major crevices...

458
00:36:02,205 --> 00:36:04,596
...between my toes
and in my belly button...

459
00:36:04,815 --> 00:36:07,206
...which I never did before
but enjoyed.

460
00:36:07,728 --> 00:36:12,686
I washed my hair with adult formula
shampoo and used creme rinse.

461
00:36:13,860 --> 00:36:17,121
I can't find my toothbrush,
so I'll pick one up today.

462
00:36:17,340 --> 00:36:19,427
Other than that, I'm in good shape.

463
00:37:10,049 --> 00:37:13,267
All right! Buzz's life savings.

464
00:37:40,057 --> 00:37:42,753
I thought the Murphys
went to Florida.

465
00:37:59,193 --> 00:38:02,150
You're one of the great
cat burglars of the world.

466
00:38:02,324 --> 00:38:04,976
You think you can keep it
down a little in there?

467
00:38:05,586 --> 00:38:09,370
<i>You've reached the Murphy's.
Please leave a message after the beep.</i>

468
00:38:10,282 --> 00:38:14,196
<i>This is Peter McCallister again.
We're in Paris at my brother's.</i>

469
00:38:14,415 --> 00:38:17,850
<i>Let me give you the number here.
The country code is 33.</i>

470
00:38:18,024 --> 00:38:22,981
<i>The area code is 1-4 and the number
is 694-876...</i>

471
00:38:23,416 --> 00:38:25,286
- Hey, Harry.
- Yeah?

472
00:38:25,548 --> 00:38:28,939
That house we ran last night,
was that the McCallister's?

473
00:38:30,332 --> 00:38:33,637
<i>- Call me in Paris.
- You're right. They're gone.</i>

474
00:38:37,029 --> 00:38:40,595
- I knew they were.
- Silver tuna tonight.

475
00:38:42,466 --> 00:38:43,814
Wow!

476
00:38:49,772 --> 00:38:51,076
How may I help you?

477
00:38:51,685 --> 00:38:55,033
Is this toothbrush approved
by the American Dental Association?

478
00:38:55,817 --> 00:38:57,425
Well, I don't know.

479
00:38:58,469 --> 00:39:00,165
It doesn't say, hon.

480
00:39:00,470 --> 00:39:01,818
Can you please find out?

481
00:39:04,950 --> 00:39:06,689
- Herb.
- Yeah?

482
00:39:06,907 --> 00:39:10,168
I got a question here
about a toothbrush.

483
00:39:16,736 --> 00:39:21,389
Do you know, is this brush approved
by the American Dental Association?

484
00:39:21,650 --> 00:39:22,606
I don't know.

485
00:39:45,134 --> 00:39:47,525
Oh, hon, you pay for that here.

486
00:39:49,613 --> 00:39:51,483
Wait, you have to pay for that.

487
00:39:52,267 --> 00:39:54,527
Son! Son!

488
00:39:55,789 --> 00:39:58,267
Jimmy, stop that boy!

489
00:40:02,617 --> 00:40:03,834
Hey!

490
00:40:08,140 --> 00:40:09,662
Shoplifter!

491
00:40:13,490 --> 00:40:14,751
Hey! Hey, kid!

492
00:40:21,797 --> 00:40:23,101
Come back here!

493
00:40:24,580 --> 00:40:26,276
Stop it, will you?

494
00:40:26,798 --> 00:40:27,972
Come here.

495
00:41:06,069 --> 00:41:07,894
I'm a criminal.

496
00:41:35,295 --> 00:41:36,208
What's so funny?

497
00:41:37,861 --> 00:41:39,077
What's so funny?

498
00:41:39,644 --> 00:41:40,687
Why are you laughing?

499
00:41:44,036 --> 00:41:45,297
You did it again.

500
00:41:46,646 --> 00:41:48,080
You left the water running.

501
00:41:49,038 --> 00:41:51,516
Why do you do that?
I told you not to do it.

