00:41:51,646 --> 00:41:54,037
- It's our calling card.
- Calling card.

503
00:41:54,256 --> 00:41:56,430
All the great ones leave their mark.

504
00:41:56,605 --> 00:41:58,213
We're the wet bandits.

505
00:41:58,605 --> 00:42:01,171
You're sick, you know?
You're really sick.

506
00:42:01,998 --> 00:42:03,781
- I'm not sick.
- Yes, you are.

507
00:42:03,997 --> 00:42:05,214
It's a sick thing to do.

508
00:42:12,043 --> 00:42:13,913
- We don't need that.
- Don't tell me...

509
00:42:14,044 --> 00:42:15,957
I can do it if I want to.

510
00:42:18,045 --> 00:42:20,350
It's not sick. Hey, watch out!

511
00:42:28,613 --> 00:42:30,048
Hey! Hey!

512
00:42:30,266 --> 00:42:32,179
You've gotta watch for traffic.

513
00:42:32,527 --> 00:42:34,440
- Sorry.
- Damn.

514
00:42:34,615 --> 00:42:37,050
Santy don't visit
the funeral homes, buddy.

515
00:42:38,050 --> 00:42:39,354
Okay, okay.

516
00:42:40,224 --> 00:42:42,311
Merry Christmas.

517
00:42:52,402 --> 00:42:53,792
What's the matter?

518
00:42:54,142 --> 00:42:56,533
I don't like the way
that kid looked at me.

519
00:42:56,752 --> 00:43:00,143
- Ever seen him before?
- I saw a hundred kids this week.

520
00:43:01,143 --> 00:43:02,926
Let's see what house he goes into.

521
00:43:35,501 --> 00:43:36,849
Why's he going faster?

522
00:43:37,022 --> 00:43:39,109
I told you something's wrong.

523
00:43:39,371 --> 00:43:41,328
He looked at me weird.
Why would he run?

524
00:44:17,468 --> 00:44:19,208
Maybe he went in the church.

525
00:44:19,513 --> 00:44:22,252
- I'm not going in there.
- Me neither.

526
00:44:22,557 --> 00:44:23,688
Let's get out of here.

527
00:44:42,518 --> 00:44:45,823
When those guys come back,
I'll be ready.

528
00:45:10,961 --> 00:45:12,047
Did they come back?

529
00:45:12,527 --> 00:45:14,310
From Paris?

530
00:45:49,928 --> 00:45:52,319
We'll come back tomorrow.
Maybe they'll be gone.

531
00:45:53,103 --> 00:45:55,625
We better go before somebody sees us.

532
00:46:27,286 --> 00:46:29,243
Look what I found in the kitchen.

533
00:46:29,460 --> 00:46:31,591
Frank, those are for later.

534
00:46:36,332 --> 00:46:38,723
Do you want a little shrimp, huh?

535
00:46:39,854 --> 00:46:41,594
Do you speak English?

536
00:46:45,116 --> 00:46:46,464
Well, is there...

537
00:46:52,249 --> 00:46:55,467
- Did you get anybody?
- I am looking for my son!

538
00:46:55,684 --> 00:46:57,336
No, I can't find anybody.

539
00:46:57,555 --> 00:47:00,686
They're all shopping.
Nobody's home for the holidays.

540
00:47:00,860 --> 00:47:02,468
Never mind, forget it.

541
00:47:03,469 --> 00:47:06,121
- This is so pointless.
- What?

542
00:47:06,644 --> 00:47:08,731
We're here rotting in this apartment.

543
00:47:08,949 --> 00:47:11,167
Kevin's at home.
Mom's at the airport.

544
00:47:11,428 --> 00:47:14,124
- So?
- You're not worried about Kevin?

545
00:47:14,342 --> 00:47:19,213
Why should I be? He acted like a jerk
and now he caught it in the butt.

546
00:47:20,430 --> 00:47:22,213
He's so little and helpless.

547
00:47:22,387 --> 00:47:23,822
Don't you think he's freaked?

548
00:47:24,040 --> 00:47:27,084
The trout can use a couple of days
in the real world.

549
00:47:27,302 --> 00:47:29,563
You're not worried
something might happen?

550
00:47:30,390 --> 00:47:32,347
No. For three reasons:

551
00:47:32,564 --> 00:47:37,217
A. I'm not that lucky.
Two: We have smoke detectors...

552
00:47:37,435 --> 00:47:41,349
...and D: We live in the most boring
street in the United States...

553
00:47:41,567 --> 00:47:45,828
...where nothing even remotely
dangerous will ever happen. Period.

554
00:48:13,010 --> 00:48:13,966
<i>Who is it?</i>

555
00:48:14,140 --> 00:48:16,401
It's Little Nero's.
I have your pizza.

556
00:48:16,967 --> 00:48:19,620
<i>Leave it on the doorstep
and get out of here.</i>

557
00:48:20,577 --> 00:48:22,055
Okay.

558
00:48:23,491 --> 00:48:24,795
What about the money?

559
00:48:26,231 --> 00:48:27,666
<i>What money?</i>

560
00:48:28,623 --> 00:48:31,145
Well, you have to pay
for your pizza, sir.

561
00:48:32,146 --> 00:48:35,494
<i>Is that a fact?
How much do I owe you?</i>

562
00:48:36,973 --> 00:48:38,843
That'll be $11.80, sir.

563
00:48:46,236 --> 00:48:48,932
<i>Keep the change, you filthy animal.</i>

564
00:48:50,846 --> 00:48:52,542
<i>- Cheapskate.
- Hey.</i>

565
00:48:52,759 --> 00:48:55,064
<i>I'm gonna give you
to the count of ten...</i>

566
00:48:55,239 --> 00:48:57,673
<i>... to get your ugly, yellow...</i>

567
00:48:57,892 --> 00:48:59,979
<i>... no-good keister
off my property...</i>

568
00:49:00,196 --> 00:49:02,283
<i>... before I pump you full of lead.</i>

569
00:49:02,501 --> 00:49:05,197
<i>One, two... ten.</i>

570
00:49:33,292 --> 00:49:36,467
A lovely cheese pizza, just for me.

571
00:49:39,859 --> 00:49:41,425
<i>- To Dallas/Forth Worth.</i>

572
00:49:41,643 --> 00:49:43,468
<i>American Airlines...</i>

573
00:49:45,209 --> 00:49:47,687
So we have the $500,
the pocket translator...

574
00:49:47,948 --> 00:49:50,296
...the two first-class seats,
that's an upgrade...

575
00:49:50,514 --> 00:49:51,688
Is that a real Rolex?

576
00:49:53,428 --> 00:49:55,733
- Do you think it is?
- No.

577
00:49:55,951 --> 00:49:59,168
But who can tell?
I also have a ring.

578
00:49:59,343 --> 00:50:01,300
Oh, that is beautiful!

579
00:50:01,430 --> 00:50:02,734
They're boarding.

580
00:50:03,344 --> 00:50:06,605
She's offered us two first-class
tickets if we go Friday.

581
00:50:06,823 --> 00:50:11,084
Plus a ring, a watch,
a pocket translator, $500 and...

582
00:50:11,303 --> 00:50:12,563
The earrings.

583
00:50:12,868 --> 00:50:16,652
She's got her own earrings.
A whole shoebox full of them.

584
00:50:16,826 --> 00:50:18,434
- Come on, come on.
- No, but...

585
00:50:19,957 --> 00:50:20,869
I'm desperate.

586
00:50:21,957 --> 00:50:25,784
I'm begging you.
From a mother to a mother. Please!

587
00:50:27,873 --> 00:50:30,525
- Oh, Ed.
- Please!

588
00:50:31,525 --> 00:50:33,264
Oh, all right.

589
00:50:39,006 --> 00:50:41,484
<i>"Dear Santa, I got a little sister
last year.</i>

590
00:50:41,702 --> 00:50:44,268
<i>This year I'd rather have
some Clay-Doh. "</i>

591
00:50:58,184 --> 00:50:59,271
I didn't mean it.

592
00:50:59,446 --> 00:51:02,533
If you come back, I'll never be
a pain in the butt again.

593
00:51:02,882 --> 00:51:06,099
I promise. Good night.

594
00:51:25,584 --> 00:51:28,758
<i>I'm dreaming</i>

595
00:51:28,976 --> 00:51:30,193
<i>Of a white</i>

596
00:51:31,324 --> 00:51:33,324
<i>Christmas</i>

597
00:51:33,542 --> 00:51:37,760
<i>Just like the ones
I used to know</i>

598
00:51:39,935 --> 00:51:43,719
<i>Where those treetops glisten</i>

599
00:51:43,936 --> 00:51:47,633
<i>And children listen</i>

600
00:51:47,894 --> 00:51:52,808
<i>To hear sleigh bells
In the snow</i>

601
00:51:53,503 --> 00:51:55,199
<i>The snow</i>

602
00:52:47,344 --> 00:52:49,214
Are those microwave dinners good?

603
00:52:49,954 --> 00:52:52,606
- I don't know.
- I'll give them a whirl.

604
00:52:58,174 --> 00:52:59,652
For the kids.

605
00:53:02,000 --> 00:53:04,174
Hold on, I got a coupon for that.

606
00:53:05,523 --> 00:53:07,393
It was in the paper this morning.

607
00:53:11,090 --> 00:53:12,003
$19.83.

608
00:53:12,656 --> 00:53:13,916
Okay.

609
00:53:18,005 --> 00:53:19,395
Are you here all by yourself?

610
00:53:20,875 --> 00:53:22,484
Ma'am, I'm 8 years old.

611
00:53:22,701 --> 00:53:27,006
You think I'd be here alone?
I don't think so.

612
00:53:27,920 --> 00:53:28,789
Where's your mom?

613
00:53:29,008 --> 00:53:30,573
- In the car.
- Where's your dad?

614
00:53:30,791 --> 00:53:33,704
- He's at work.
- What about brothers and sisters?

615
00:53:33,922 --> 00:53:35,226
I'm an only child.

616
00:53:35,749 --> 00:53:37,879
- Where do you live?
- I can't tell you.

617
00:53:38,053 --> 00:53:40,923
- Why not?
- Cause you're a stranger.

618
00:54:19,587 --> 00:54:22,761
<i>Hello, Kevin!</i>

619
00:54:26,240 --> 00:54:27,501
Shut up!

620
00:54:41,157 --> 00:54:42,418
I don't get it.

621
00:54:43,071 --> 00:54:45,202
It looks like there's nobody's home.

622
00:54:46,202 --> 00:54:48,289
Last night the place is jumping.

623
00:54:48,986 --> 00:54:50,638
Something ain't right.

624
00:54:51,639 --> 00:54:52,682
Go check it out.

625
00:55:01,684 --> 00:55:02,771
Now?

626
00:55:03,294 --> 00:55:06,816
No, tomorrow, egghead!
Now! Go ahead.

627
00:55:09,122 --> 00:55:10,252
"Now."

628
00:55:27,605 --> 00:55:28,691
Shit!

629
00:55:31,997 --> 00:55:33,563
<i>Get the hell out of here.</i>

630
00:55:33,780 --> 00:55:36,911
<i>All right, Johnny.
But what about my money?</i>

631
00:55:37,129 --> 00:55:38,172
<i>What money?</i>

632
00:55:38,390 --> 00:55:40,607
<i>A.C. Said you had
some dough for me.</i>

633
00:55:40,782 --> 00:55:43,696
<i>Is that a fact?
How much do I owe you?</i>

634
00:55:43,870 --> 00:55:45,653
<i>A.C. Said ten percent.</i>

635
00:55:46,914 --> 00:55:49,480
<i>Too bad A.C.
Ain't in charge no more.</i>

636
00:55:49,611 --> 00:55:50,785
<i>What do you mean?</i>

637
00:55:51,003 --> 00:55:53,525
<i>He's upstairs, taking a bath.</i>

638
00:55:54,438 --> 00:55:56,525
<i>He'll call you when he gets out.</i>

639
00:55:58,004 --> 00:56:02,221
<i>Hey, I tell you what I'm
gonna give you, Snakes.</i>

640
00:56:02,919 --> 00:56:06,136
<i>- Snakes?
- I'll give you to the count of ten...</i>

641
00:56:06,355 --> 00:56:08,572
<i>... to get your ugly,
yellow, no-good...</i>

642
00:56:08,789 --> 00:56:10,746
<i>... keister off my property...</i>

643
00:56:10,964 --> 00:56:13,007
<i>... before I pump you full of lead.</i>

644
00:56:13,182 --> 00:56:15,878
<i>All right, Johnny. I'm sorry.
I'm going.</i>

645
00:56:16,096 --> 00:56:18,923
<i>One, two... ten.</i>

646
00:56:38,232 --> 00:56:41,189
<i>Keep the change, you filthy animal.</i>

647
00:56:45,973 --> 00:56:46,799
What happened?

648
00:56:47,017 --> 00:56:49,713
I don't know who, but somebody
just got blown away.

649
00:56:49,932 --> 00:56:52,280
Somebody beat us,
they're in there.

650
00:56:52,497 --> 00:56:53,628
Two of them.

651
00:56:53,802 --> 00:56:56,454
There was arguing.
One blew the other one away.

652
00:56:56,672 --> 00:56:58,238
- Who?
- I don't know.

653
00:56:59,151 --> 00:57:04,065
I recognized one of their voices.
I heard that name "Snakes" before.

654
00:57:04,283 --> 00:57:08,023
Snakes? Snakes. Snakes.
I don't know no Snakes.

655
00:57:08,197 --> 00:57:11,546
Snakes. Let's get out of here.

656
00:57:13,850 --> 00:57:15,111
Hold it. Hold it.

657
00:57:15,286 --> 00:57:18,634
Let's wait and see who it is.
We work this neighborhood too.

658
00:57:19,461 --> 00:57:21,460
Suppose the cops finger us
for a job...

659
00:57:21,679 --> 00:57:24,679
...and they ask us about
a murder in the area.

660
00:57:24,897 --> 00:57:27,854
Wouldn't it be nice to have
a face to go with it?

661
00:57:30,464 --> 00:57:31,681
That's a good idea.

662
00:57:32,203 --> 00:57:35,247
Of course it's a good idea.
Snakes?

663
00:57:35,465 --> 00:57:37,596
He sounded like a snake.

664
00:57:44,250 --> 00:57:45,424
Everything's full.

665
00:57:45,642 --> 00:57:47,076
Everything's full?

666
00:57:47,294 --> 00:57:50,164
I'm very sorry, but
it is Christmas Eve.

667
00:57:50,904 --> 00:57:52,643
What about another airline?

668
00:57:57,384 --> 00:58:00,210
Nothing available.
May I help you get a hotel room?

669
00:58:00,385 --> 00:58:02,342
Tomorrow we can get you a flight.

670
00:58:02,560 --> 00:58:04,255
I can't wait that long.

671
00:58:04,516 --> 00:58:08,474
I'm sorry, ma'am, but we're
doing absolutely everything we can.

672
00:58:12,649 --> 00:58:15,693
I'm in your way. I'm sorry.
You've places to go.

673
00:58:15,911 --> 00:58:18,302
Got a ticket there, good. Excuse me.

674
00:58:18,521 --> 00:58:21,869
Look, I have been awake
for almost 60 hours.

675
00:58:22,087 --> 00:58:23,565
I'm tired and I'm dirty.

676
00:58:23,782 --> 00:58:27,870
I have been from Chicago to Paris,
to Dallas, to... Where am I?

677
00:58:28,436 --> 00:58:29,740
Scranton.

678
00:58:30,306 --> 00:58:32,784
I'm trying to get home
to my 8-year-old son.

679
00:58:33,698 --> 00:58:36,132
Now you're telling me it's hopeless?

680
00:58:36,351 --> 00:58:38,829
- I'm sorry.
- No. No way.

681
00:58:39,048 --> 00:58:40,135
This is Christmas!

682
00:58:40,352 --> 00:58:42,787
The season of perpetual hope.

683
00:58:43,005 --> 00:58:45,919
If I have to get on
your runway and hitchhike...

684
00:58:46,136 --> 00:58:48,093
...if it costs me everything I own...

685
00:58:48,311 --> 00:58:51,181
...if I have to sell my soul
to the Devil himself...

686
00:58:51,399 --> 00:58:54,182
...I am going to get home to my son.

687
00:58:55,530 --> 00:58:57,487
Ma'am, if there was anything...

688
00:58:57,705 --> 00:58:59,183
Do it. Do anything.

689
00:58:59,444 --> 00:59:01,401
- I can get you a hotel room.
- What?

690
00:59:01,662 --> 00:59:05,662
Can you excuse us for a sec?
Can I see you for a second, please?

691
00:59:05,881 --> 00:59:07,794
Excuse us.

692
00:59:09,882 --> 00:59:12,273
You got a little bit of a dilemma.

693
00:59:12,492 --> 00:59:14,926
We got a crisis ourselves.

694
00:59:15,405 --> 00:59:17,710
Allow me to introduce myself.
Gus Polinski.

695
00:59:20,233 --> 00:59:22,363
Polka King of the Midwest?

696
00:59:25,582 --> 00:59:27,843
The Kenosha Kickers?

697
00:59:28,452 --> 00:59:29,756
- Hi there.
- Hiya.

698
00:59:30,583 --> 00:59:34,018
That's okay. I thought you might
have recognized...

699
00:59:34,236 --> 00:59:37,845
I had a few hits a few years ago.
That's why I just...

700
00:59:38,063 --> 00:59:42,716
<i>"Polka, Polka, Polka"?
Polka, polka, polka</i>

701
00:59:42,891 --> 00:59:43,890
"Twin Lakes Polka"?

702
00:59:44,109 --> 00:59:48,935
"Yamahoozie Polka," a.k.a.
"Kiss Me Polka"? "Polka Twist"?

703
00:59:49,153 --> 00:59:50,631
These are songs?

704
00:59:50,849 --> 00:59:53,763
Yeah. Yeah, we...
Some fairly big hits for us.

705
00:59:53,980 --> 00:59:55,763
You know, in the early '80s.

706
00:59:56,025 --> 00:59:58,808
Yeah, we sold about 623
copies of that.

707
00:59:59,026 --> 01:00:00,547
- In Chicago?
- No, Sheboygan.

708
01:00:00,809 --> 01:00:02,374
Very big in Sheboygan.

709
01:00:02,635 --> 01:00:04,157
Did you say you could help?

710
01:00:04,331 --> 01:00:08,115
Anyway, I'm rambling on here.
Our flight was canceled...

711
01:00:08,246 --> 01:00:12,681
...so we're gonna drive. See the guy
in the yellow jacket over there?

712
01:00:12,942 --> 01:00:16,334
He's gonna rent us a nice big van
to drive to Milwaukee.

713
01:00:16,508 --> 01:00:19,813
Now, I heard you had some problems
getting to Chicago?

714
01:00:20,248 --> 01:00:21,596
To see your kid or something?

715
01:00:21,771 --> 01:00:25,641
Uh, my son. He...
We left, and he's there.

716
01:00:25,859 --> 01:00:29,555
If you have to get to Chicago,
we'll gladly drive you.

717
01:00:29,686 --> 01:00:31,729
It's on the way to Milwaukee.

718
01:00:32,296 --> 01:00:34,686
- You'd give me a ride?
- Sure, why not?

719
01:00:34,861 --> 01:00:36,427
You've got to get home.

720
01:00:36,644 --> 01:00:39,602
- A ride to Chicago?
- Sure, it's Christmastime.

721
01:00:40,298 --> 01:00:41,820
Thank you. Oh, thank you.

722
01:00:42,037 --> 01:00:44,212
You don't mind going with polka bums?

723
01:00:44,429 --> 01:00:46,212
No, I'd love to.

724
01:01:08,653 --> 01:01:11,349
Hey, Marv. Marv, Marv!

725
01:01:11,523 --> 01:01:12,393
Look at this.

726
01:01:19,091 --> 01:01:22,787
I think we're getting scammed
by a kindergartner.

727
01:01:53,186 --> 01:01:55,403
Dad, can you come here
and help me?

728
01:02:00,276 --> 01:02:02,493
Remember that kid
we saw the other day?

729
01:02:03,494 --> 01:02:04,972
He lives here.

730
01:02:05,277 --> 01:02:07,755
If the kid's here,
the parent's got to be.

731
01:02:08,408 --> 01:02:09,974
He's home alone.

732
01:02:17,976 --> 01:02:20,193
What? You want to come
back tonight?

733
01:02:20,412 --> 01:02:21,846
Even with the kid here?

734
01:02:22,063 --> 01:02:24,107
I don't think that's a good idea.

735
01:02:24,325 --> 01:02:27,065
That house is the reason
we worked this block.

736
01:02:27,282 --> 01:02:29,631
Ever since I saw that house,
I wanted it.

737
01:02:29,806 --> 01:02:31,893
Let's take it one step at a time.

738
01:02:32,110 --> 01:02:36,763
We'll unload the van, get a bite
to eat, we'll come back about 9:00.

739
01:02:36,938 --> 01:02:38,198
Nine o'clock.

740
01:02:38,372 --> 01:02:39,764
This way it's dark then.

741
01:02:39,981 --> 01:02:42,981
Yeah, kids are scared of the dark.

742
01:02:43,200 --> 01:02:45,939
You're afraid of the dark too.
You know you are.

743
01:02:47,331 --> 01:02:48,765
No, I'm not.

744
01:02:48,984 --> 01:02:50,853
- Yes, you are.
- Not, not, not.

745
01:02:51,028 --> 01:02:52,159
You are so.

746
01:02:52,332 --> 01:02:54,332
Mom, where are you?

747
01:03:09,120 --> 01:03:10,337
Do you play?

748
01:03:10,990 --> 01:03:14,382
Do you want to try? Go ahead,
try it. Try it!

749
01:03:41,911 --> 01:03:44,259
- Excuse me.
- Yeah?

750
01:03:45,782 --> 01:03:47,521
Hey, nice shoes.

751
01:03:47,869 --> 01:03:49,347
Oh, thanks.

752
01:03:49,566 --> 01:03:53,174
Is he still here? It's really
important that I see him.

753
01:03:53,827 --> 01:03:57,349
He's getting in his car.
If you hurry, you can catch him.

754
01:03:58,698 --> 01:04:02,916
How low! Giving Kriss Kringle
a parking ticket on Christmas Eve!

755
01:04:03,135 --> 01:04:05,743
What's next, rabies shots
for the Easter Bunny?

756
01:04:05,962 --> 01:04:07,440
Santa, hold on.

757
01:04:09,788 --> 01:04:11,788
- Can I talk to you for a minute?
- Quickly.

758
01:04:12,006 --> 01:04:13,658
Santa's running late.

759
01:04:13,833 --> 01:04:16,311
I know you're not
the real Santa Claus.

760
01:04:16,790 --> 01:04:20,313
Huh, what makes you say that?
Just out of curiosity.

761
01:04:20,530 --> 01:04:23,921
- I'm old enough to know how it works.
- All right.

762
01:04:24,140 --> 01:04:26,183
But I also know you work for him.

763
01:04:26,576 --> 01:04:29,359
- I'd like you to give him a message.
- Shoot.

764
01:04:29,838 --> 01:04:34,534
Kevin McCallister, 681 Lincoln Blvd.
Do you need the phone number?

765
01:04:34,926 --> 01:04:36,186
No, that's all right.

766
01:04:36,491 --> 01:04:38,274
This is extremely important.

767
01:04:38,448 --> 01:04:43,406
Please tell him instead of presents,
I just want my family back.

768
01:04:44,146 --> 01:04:48,537
No toys. Nothing but Peter, Kate,
Buzz, Megan, Linnie and Jeff.

769
01:04:48,756 --> 01:04:50,755
And my aunt and my cousins.

770
01:04:50,973 --> 01:04:54,104
And if he has time,
my Uncle Frank. Okay?

771
01:04:55,801 --> 01:04:56,931
Okay.

772
01:04:57,889 --> 01:05:00,193
- I'll see what I can do.
- Thanks.

773
01:05:00,411 --> 01:05:04,846
Wait. My elf took the last of the
candy canes home to her boyfriend.

774
01:05:05,064 --> 01:05:06,978
- That's okay.
- No, don't be silly.

775
01:05:07,195 --> 01:05:10,065
Everybody who sees Santa
has got to get something.

776
01:05:10,282 --> 01:05:14,414
Here, hold out your little paw there.
There you go.

777
01:05:14,850 --> 01:05:17,198
- Don't spoil your dinner.
- I won't.

778
01:05:17,676 --> 01:05:19,024
Thanks.

779
01:05:30,245 --> 01:05:31,810
Son of a...!

780
01:08:29,206 --> 01:08:30,596
Merry Christmas.

781
01:08:33,077 --> 01:08:34,337
May I sit down?

782
01:08:45,689 --> 01:08:47,123
That's my granddaughter.

783
01:08:47,689 --> 01:08:49,341
The little red-haired girl.

784
01:08:51,603 --> 01:08:54,387
She's about your age.
You know her?

785
01:08:54,648 --> 01:08:55,605
No.

786
01:08:55,822 --> 01:08:57,648
You live next to me, don't you?

787
01:08:59,039 --> 01:09:02,606
You can say hello when you see me.
You don't have to be afraid.

788
01:09:03,693 --> 01:09:08,520
There's a lot of things going around
about me, but none of it's true. Okay?

789
01:09:09,390 --> 01:09:11,565
- You've been good this year?
- I think so.

790
01:09:12,087 --> 01:09:13,391
You swear to it?

791
01:09:14,000 --> 01:09:14,999
No.

792
01:09:15,174 --> 01:09:19,827
Yeah. Well, this is the place to be
if you're feeling bad about yourself.

793
01:09:20,176 --> 01:09:22,828
- It is?
- I think so.

794
01:09:23,047 --> 01:09:25,612
- Are you feeling bad about yourself?
- No.

795
01:09:30,049 --> 01:09:32,136
I've been kind of a pain lately.

796
01:09:32,614 --> 01:09:35,049
I said some things I shouldn't have.

797
01:09:35,268 --> 01:09:38,007
I really haven't been
too good this year.

798
01:09:38,659 --> 01:09:39,615
Yeah.

799
01:09:39,790 --> 01:09:43,051
I'm kind of upset
because I really like my family.

800
01:09:43,313 --> 01:09:48,183
Even though sometimes I say I don't.
Sometimes I even think I don't.

801
01:09:48,575 --> 01:09:51,271
- Do you get that?
- I think so.

802
01:09:51,533 --> 01:09:53,967
How you feel about family
is a complicated thing.

803
01:09:54,794 --> 01:09:57,185
Especially with an older brother.

804
01:09:57,968 --> 01:10:00,273
Deep down, you'll always love him.

805
01:10:00,491 --> 01:10:04,840
But you can forget that you love him.
You can hurt them, they can hurt you.

806
01:10:05,014 --> 01:10:07,014
That's not just because you're young.

807
01:10:09,145 --> 01:10:11,841
You want to know the real
reason why I'm here?

808
01:10:12,060 --> 01:10:13,277
Sure.

809
01:10:13,712 --> 01:10:15,755
I came to hear my granddaughter sing.

810
01:10:16,104 --> 01:10:17,669
I can't come hear her tonight.

811
01:10:18,148 --> 01:10:19,191
You have plans?

812
01:10:19,670 --> 01:10:20,757
No.

813
01:10:21,714 --> 01:10:23,018
I'm not welcome.

814
01:10:23,758 --> 01:10:25,019
At church?

815
01:10:25,236 --> 01:10:27,324
You're always welcome at church.

816
01:10:27,586 --> 01:10:29,585
I'm not welcome with my son.

817
01:10:31,108 --> 01:10:34,804
Years back, before you and your family
moved on the block...

818
01:10:35,588 --> 01:10:37,240
...I had an argument with my son.

819
01:10:38,066 --> 01:10:39,197
How old is he?

820
01:10:39,414 --> 01:10:40,936
He's grown up.

821
01:10:42,372 --> 01:10:47,024
We lost our tempers, and I said
I didn't care to see him anymore.

822
01:10:47,547 --> 01:10:51,852
He said the same, and we haven't
spoken to each other since.

823
01:10:52,983 --> 01:10:55,288
If you miss him,
why don't you call him?

824
01:10:55,854 --> 01:10:58,029
I'm afraid if I call,
he won't talk to me.

825
01:10:58,246 --> 01:10:59,768
How do you know?

826
01:11:00,768 --> 01:11:02,160
I don't know.

827
01:11:02,421 --> 01:11:03,552
I'm just afraid.

828
01:11:04,160 --> 01:11:07,291
No offense, but aren't you
a little old to be afraid?

829
01:11:08,597 --> 01:11:10,771
You can be old for a lot of things.

830
01:11:10,989 --> 01:11:13,772
- You're never too old to be afraid.
- That's true.

831
01:11:13,990 --> 01:11:15,903
I was afraid of our basement.

832
01:11:16,120 --> 01:11:19,381
It's dark. There's weird stuff
down there, and it smells funny.

833
01:11:19,599 --> 01:11:23,208
That sort of thing.
It's bothered me for years.

834
01:11:23,426 --> 01:11:24,731
Basements are like that.

835
01:11:25,992 --> 01:11:28,427
I made myself go down
to do some laundry...

836
01:11:28,602 --> 01:11:30,732
...and I found out it's not so bad.

837
01:11:30,950 --> 01:11:35,603
I worried about it, but if you
turn on the lights, it's no big deal.

838
01:11:35,951 --> 01:11:36,908
What's your point?

839
01:11:37,343 --> 01:11:40,126
My point is,
you should call your son.

840
01:11:41,084 --> 01:11:43,824
- What if he won't talk to me?
- At least you'll know.

841
01:11:44,041 --> 01:11:48,433
Then you could stop worrying about it.
You won't have to be afraid anymore.

842
01:11:49,216 --> 01:11:54,130
No matter how mad I was, I'd talk to
Dad. Especially around the holidays.

843
01:11:55,913 --> 01:11:57,435
I don't know.

844
01:11:57,697 --> 01:11:58,783
Just give it a shot.

845
01:11:59,002 --> 01:12:00,610
For your granddaughter anyway.

846
01:12:00,828 --> 01:12:04,089
I'm sure she misses you.
And the presents.

847
01:12:04,611 --> 01:12:06,046
I send her a check.

848
01:12:06,743 --> 01:12:08,569
I wish my grandparents did that.

849
01:12:08,786 --> 01:12:10,264
They always send me clothes.

850
01:12:10,483 --> 01:12:13,440
Last year I got a sweater
with a bird knitted on it.

851
01:12:13,657 --> 01:12:14,658
Oh, that's nice.

852
01:12:14,875 --> 01:12:16,962
Not for a guy in the second grade.

853
01:12:17,224 --> 01:12:19,832
You can get beat up for wearing
something like that.

854
01:12:21,181 --> 01:12:23,224
I have a friend who got nailed...

855
01:12:23,443 --> 01:12:26,356
...because there was a rumor
he wore dinosaur pajamas.

856
01:12:27,487 --> 01:12:29,661
You better run home where you belong.

857
01:12:30,531 --> 01:12:31,662
Think about what I said.

858
01:12:32,097 --> 01:12:33,619
- All right?
- Okay.

859
01:12:34,446 --> 01:12:35,533
It's nice talking to you.

860
01:12:36,577 --> 01:12:38,229
Nice talking to you.

861
01:12:44,622 --> 01:12:46,839
- What about you?
- Me?

862
01:12:47,319 --> 01:12:48,884
Yeah. You and your son.

863
01:12:50,841 --> 01:12:52,711
We'll see what happens.

864
01:12:54,060 --> 01:12:55,364
Merry Christmas.

865
01:12:56,452 --> 01:12:58,365
Merry Christmas.

866
01:13:50,379 --> 01:13:53,945
This is my house.
I have to defend it.

867
01:15:21,882 --> 01:15:24,926
We'll check it out.
We can come back for the truck.

868
01:15:33,233 --> 01:15:34,537
How do you want to go in?

869
01:15:35,016 --> 01:15:37,973
We'll go to the back door.
Maybe he'll let us in.

870
01:15:38,191 --> 01:15:41,582
Yeah, he's a kid. Kids are stupid.

871
01:15:43,670 --> 01:15:47,584
Bless this nutritious, microwaveable
macaroni and cheese dinner...

872
01:15:47,845 --> 01:15:50,454
...and the people who sold
it on sale.

873
01:16:15,636 --> 01:16:18,419
This is it. Don't get scared now.

874
01:16:31,509 --> 01:16:34,162
Merry Christmas, little fella.

875
01:16:35,076 --> 01:16:39,858
We know that you're in there,
and that you're all alone.

876
01:16:40,337 --> 01:16:42,554
Yeah, come on, kid. Open up.

877
01:16:43,599 --> 01:16:46,165
It's Santy Claus and his elf.

878
01:16:48,645 --> 01:16:50,253
We're not gonna hurt you.

879
01:16:50,471 --> 01:16:53,950
No, no. Got some nice
presents for you.

880
01:16:54,298 --> 01:16:57,906
Be a good little fella now
and open the door.

881
01:17:02,691 --> 01:17:03,865
What?

882
01:17:05,692 --> 01:17:07,649
What? What?

883
01:17:08,563 --> 01:17:09,476
What?

884
01:17:09,606 --> 01:17:11,911
- What happened?
- Get that little...

885
01:17:23,654 --> 01:17:25,044
Hello.

886
01:17:30,786 --> 01:17:33,090
Yes! Yes!

887
01:17:33,308 --> 01:17:34,874
The little jerk is armed!

888
01:17:35,048 --> 01:17:39,266
That's it! I'm going in the front.
You go down the basement!

889
01:20:12,003 --> 01:20:16,743
Oh, boy. That's it, you little...
You little...

890
01:20:17,657 --> 01:20:19,788
No, not this time, you little brat.

891
01:20:23,224 --> 01:20:26,093
You little creep, where are you?

892
01:20:50,013 --> 01:20:51,405
Yes!

893
01:21:25,153 --> 01:21:26,805
- Rip his head off...!

894
01:21:36,939 --> 01:21:38,331
You're dead, kid.

895
01:22:25,648 --> 01:22:28,431
Where are you, you little creep?!

896
01:22:44,740 --> 01:22:47,436
Harry, I'm coming in!

897
01:22:52,003 --> 01:22:54,134
Oh, no! I'm really scared.

898
01:22:54,351 --> 01:22:58,221
It's too late for you, kid, we're
in the house. We're gonna get you.

899
01:22:58,439 --> 01:23:00,526
Okay, come and get me!

900
01:23:00,875 --> 01:23:01,918
Why, you...!

901
01:23:08,529 --> 01:23:09,790
Now you're dead!

902
01:23:35,492 --> 01:23:38,058
I'm gonna kill that kid!

903
01:23:55,542 --> 01:23:57,325
Why'd you take your shoes off?

904
01:23:57,890 --> 01:23:59,586
Why are you dressed like a chicken?

905
01:24:01,543 --> 01:24:03,151
I'm up here, you morons.

906
01:24:03,413 --> 01:24:04,979
Come and get me.

907
01:24:08,371 --> 01:24:11,676
You guys give up, or are you
thirsty for more?

908
01:24:21,505 --> 01:24:22,853
Heads up!

909
01:24:25,941 --> 01:24:28,463
Don't worry, Marv.
I'll get him for you.

910
01:24:32,552 --> 01:24:33,551
Yes!

911
01:24:38,814 --> 01:24:41,118
He's only a kid, Harry.
We can take him.

912
01:24:41,293 --> 01:24:44,380
Ah, shut up, will you?
What is it?

913
01:24:44,598 --> 01:24:46,772
You're missing some teeth.

914
01:24:46,946 --> 01:24:49,033
Where? It's my gold tooth.

915
01:24:49,295 --> 01:24:52,295
My gold tooth. I'll kill him.
I'll kill him!

916
01:24:54,687 --> 01:24:56,862
You bomb me with
one more can, kid...

917
01:24:57,037 --> 01:25:01,298
<i>...and I'll snap off your cojones
and boil them in motor oil!</i>

918
01:25:04,647 --> 01:25:05,733
<i>911 emergency.</i>

919
01:25:05,996 --> 01:25:07,821
Hello, my house is being robbed.

920
01:25:08,039 --> 01:25:12,735
My address is 656 Lincoln Boulevard.
My name is Murphy.

921
01:25:16,302 --> 01:25:17,650
You never know what's up there.

922
01:25:18,824 --> 01:25:19,650
There he is!

923
01:25:25,305 --> 01:25:27,044
I got you! I got him, Harry.

924
01:25:28,827 --> 01:25:30,088
I got him.

925
01:25:31,307 --> 01:25:32,524
Harry, give me a hand!

926
01:25:35,873 --> 01:25:36,786
I got him!

927
01:25:38,004 --> 01:25:39,396
Harry, help me. Get up!

928
01:25:40,961 --> 01:25:42,178
I got him.

929
01:26:21,972 --> 01:26:23,059
What are you doing?

930
01:26:23,885 --> 01:26:26,581
Harry, don't move.

931
01:26:28,104 --> 01:26:30,495
Don't move.

932
01:26:30,931 --> 01:26:32,496
Marv, what are you doing?

933
01:26:37,237 --> 01:26:38,236
Did I get him?

934
01:26:39,368 --> 01:26:40,760
Did I get him?!

935
01:26:41,151 --> 01:26:43,195
Where is it? Where is it?

936
01:26:43,412 --> 01:26:47,065
Never mind that. Here!
How do you like it, huh? You jerk!

937
01:26:47,240 --> 01:26:49,979
Get that kid, before l...
Get that kid!

938
01:27:16,726 --> 01:27:18,030
Where'd he go?

939
01:27:18,770 --> 01:27:20,770
Maybe he committed suicide.

940
01:27:21,206 --> 01:27:26,076
Down here, you big horse's ass!
Come get me before I call the police.

941
01:27:26,250 --> 01:27:28,207
- Let's get him!
- Wait, wait.

942
01:27:28,468 --> 01:27:30,294
It's just what he wants us to do:

943
01:27:30,512 --> 01:27:33,643
Go back through his fun house
so we get all tore up.

944
01:27:33,861 --> 01:27:35,339
He's gonna call the cops!

945
01:27:35,557 --> 01:27:37,252
From a tree house?!

946
01:27:37,514 --> 01:27:38,645
Come on.

947
01:27:39,863 --> 01:27:41,253
Out the window?

948
01:27:41,732 --> 01:27:43,080
I'm not going out the window.

949
01:27:43,299 --> 01:27:47,212
Why, you scared? Are you afraid?
Come on, get out here.

950
01:27:52,083 --> 01:27:53,387
Come on.

951
01:27:59,434 --> 01:28:00,912
Come on!

952
01:28:06,826 --> 01:28:09,739
- Come on. Keep going.
- Let's go back, Harry.

953
01:28:15,393 --> 01:28:16,480
Shut it, Marv.

954
01:28:20,091 --> 01:28:20,960
Hey, guys!

955
01:28:21,613 --> 01:28:22,830
Check this out.

956
01:28:23,961 --> 01:28:25,700
Go back. Go back.

957
01:29:14,280 --> 01:29:15,062
There he is!

958
01:29:15,671 --> 01:29:17,846
Hey, I'm calling the cops!

959
01:29:19,106 --> 01:29:21,585
Wait, wait!
He wants us to follow him.

960
01:29:21,759 --> 01:29:23,759
I got a better idea. Come on.

961
01:29:41,722 --> 01:29:43,026
Hiya, pal.

962
01:29:43,461 --> 01:29:46,636
We outsmarted you this time.
Get over here!

963
01:29:52,594 --> 01:29:54,072
What are you gonna do, Harry?

964
01:29:54,464 --> 01:29:56,464
I'll do exactly what he did to us.

965
01:29:56,725 --> 01:29:58,508
Burn his head with a blowtorch.

966
01:29:58,726 --> 01:30:00,769
I'll smash his face with an iron.

967
01:30:00,987 --> 01:30:03,813
I'd like to slap him
in the face with a paint can!

968
01:30:04,032 --> 01:30:05,598
Shove a nail through his foot!

969
01:30:05,815 --> 01:30:10,773
I'm gonna bite off every one of
these little fingers, one at a time.

970
01:30:20,036 --> 01:30:22,427
Come on. Let's get you home.

971
01:30:45,347 --> 01:30:48,087
Wow! This is great.

972
01:30:51,436 --> 01:30:53,827
Nice move,
leaving the water running.

973
01:30:54,002 --> 01:30:57,786
Now we know each and every house
that you've hit.

974
01:31:01,264 --> 01:31:04,048
We've been looking for you guys
for a long time.

975
01:31:04,265 --> 01:31:07,135
Yeah. Well, remember,
we're the "Wet Bandits."

976
01:31:07,353 --> 01:31:11,354
- Wet Bandits, that's W-E-T...
- Shut up! Get in the car!

977
01:31:11,571 --> 01:31:13,310
Hey, come on. Come on.

978
01:31:13,963 --> 01:31:16,441
- Hand off the head, pal!
- Come on.

979
01:32:12,023 --> 01:32:14,066
<i>I'm a bad parent. I'm a bad parent.</i>

980
01:32:14,327 --> 01:32:15,414
No, you're not.

981
01:32:15,633 --> 01:32:18,285
You're beating yourself up there.
This happens.

982
01:32:18,502 --> 01:32:20,154
These things happen, you know.

983
01:32:20,373 --> 01:32:24,069
You want to talk about bad parents?
Look at us.

984
01:32:24,287 --> 01:32:29,027
We're on the road 48, 49 weeks a year.
We hardly see our families.

985
01:32:29,723 --> 01:32:32,028
Joe, over there. Gosh, you know...

986
01:32:32,201 --> 01:32:35,071
...he forgets his kids' names
half the time.

987
01:32:35,246 --> 01:32:38,637
Ziggy over there,
he's never even met his kid.

988
01:32:38,856 --> 01:32:42,682
Eddy... Let's just hope
none of them write a book about him.

989
01:32:43,857 --> 01:32:47,380
Tell me, have you gone on vacation
and left your child home?

990
01:32:50,772 --> 01:32:52,120
No.

991
01:32:52,904 --> 01:32:55,817
But I did leave one
at a funeral parlor once.

992
01:32:56,600 --> 01:32:59,905
Yeah, it was terrible too.
I was all distraught and everything.

993
01:33:00,122 --> 01:33:04,340
The wife and I, we left the little
tyke there in the funeral parlor.

994
01:33:04,558 --> 01:33:08,255
All day. You know, we went
back at night, when we...

995
01:33:08,472 --> 01:33:10,689
...came to our senses,
there he was.

996
01:33:10,864 --> 01:33:14,039
Apparently, he was there
all day with a corpse.

997
01:33:15,083 --> 01:33:18,388
Now, he was okay.
You know, after six, seven weeks.

998
01:33:18,605 --> 01:33:21,084
He came around
and started talking again.

999
01:33:22,433 --> 01:33:25,432
They get over it.
Kids are resilient like that.

1000
01:33:25,651 --> 01:33:27,347
We shouldn't talk about this.

1001
01:33:27,564 --> 01:33:29,434
I was just trying to cheer you up.

1002
01:33:29,652 --> 01:33:31,783
I'm sorry I did.

1003
01:33:58,007 --> 01:33:59,137
Mom?

1004
01:34:04,357 --> 01:34:05,574
Mom?

1005
01:34:57,980 --> 01:34:59,328
Kevin!

1006
01:35:33,338 --> 01:35:35,381
Merry Christmas, sweetheart.

1007
01:35:44,645 --> 01:35:47,254
Oh, Kevin, I'm so sorry.

1008
01:36:07,086 --> 01:36:08,955
Where's everybody else?

1009
01:36:09,695 --> 01:36:11,695
Oh, baby, they couldn't come.

1010
01:36:11,913 --> 01:36:13,087
They wanted to so much...

1011
01:36:13,349 --> 01:36:17,784
I didn't fall asleep in the back
and drool all over you, did I?

1012
01:36:18,001 --> 01:36:20,306
- You do drool!
- Shut up!

1013
01:36:23,220 --> 01:36:26,308
Kevin, my boy. How are you?

1014
01:36:27,048 --> 01:36:28,743
You're all right.

1015
01:36:29,222 --> 01:36:30,439
I love you. You okay?

1016
01:36:35,354 --> 01:36:37,962
It's cool that you didn't
burn the place down.

1017
01:36:40,529 --> 01:36:42,095
Thanks, Buzz.

1018
01:36:43,660 --> 01:36:45,747
Wait a minute.
How'd you guys get home?

1019
01:36:45,966 --> 01:36:48,532
On the morning flight you didn't
want to wait for.

1020
01:36:48,749 --> 01:36:51,924
- Oh, no. Oh! Thank you.
- Merry Christmas.

1021
01:36:52,185 --> 01:36:53,619
Merry Christmas.

1022
01:36:54,186 --> 01:36:56,316
Someone has to find an open store.

1023
01:36:56,534 --> 01:36:58,142
I went shopping yesterday.

1024
01:37:00,753 --> 01:37:02,361
You, shopping?

1025
01:37:02,578 --> 01:37:05,362
I got some milk, eggs
and fabric softener.

1026
01:37:07,232 --> 01:37:09,102
- What?
- No kidding?

1027
01:37:09,320 --> 01:37:11,103
What a funny guy.

1028
01:37:11,277 --> 01:37:13,452
What else did you do
while we were away?

1029
01:37:14,496 --> 01:37:16,800
Just hung around.

1030
01:37:18,888 --> 01:37:20,322
Bring your stuff upstairs.

1031
01:37:20,540 --> 01:37:25,019
He went shopping? He doesn't know how
to tie his shoe. He's going shopping?

1032
01:37:51,897 --> 01:37:53,462
Honey, what's this?

1033
01:38:51,870 --> 01:38:55,261
Kevin! What did you do
to my room?

